---
import BaseLayout from "~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Alexi Hart">
  <section class="py-xl">
    <div class="max-w-container-max mx-auto px-md">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-xl items-center">
        <div class="md:w-1/2">
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "")}/images/alexi-hart-professional-headshot.png`}
            alt="Alexi Hart"
            class="rounded-xl shadow-lg border-4 border-surface w-full aspect-[4/5] object-cover"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="md:w-1/2 space-y-md">
          <span class="font-label-sm text-label-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-secondary">A Note from Alexi</span>
          <h1 class="font-headline-xl text-headline-xl text-primary">Hello, friend.</h1>
          <div class="space-y-sm font-body-md text-body-md text-on-surface-variant">
            <p>I'm Alexi, and I believe that everyone deserves a happy ending, even if the road there is a little bumpy. I've been writing since I could hold a pen, but it wasn't until I moved to a small cottage that I truly found my voice.</p>
            <p>When I'm not dreaming up new ways for my characters to fall in love, you can find me scouring antique bookstores, nursing a large cup of Earl Grey, or trying (and failing) to bake the perfect macaron.</p>
            <p>My stories are inspired by the small moments: a shared glance across a crowded room, the smell of rain on pavement, and the quiet comfort of a long-term friendship. I'm so glad you're here to share them with me.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="font-headline-md text-headline-md italic text-primary pt-md">Alexi</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
